A 27-year-old woman has been arrested in Krugersdorp for allegedly abandoning her baby in a toilet.STORY UPDATE:&nbsp; Police still searching for mom who left baby in mall toilet&nbsp;She abandoned the baby at the Key West mall in Krugersdorp, last week Friday.A customer found the baby in the toilet.Captain Appel Ernst says the mother was arrested this afternoon.She will appear in the Krugersdorp Magistrate's Court on Friday to face child abandonment charges. ER24 paramedics took her to the Dr Yusuf Dadoo Hospital., where staff had named her Hope because she received help from people when it seemed as if all hope was lost.According to the Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Investigations commander, Lieutenant-Colonel Kathy Segotta, &nbsp;the baby is doing well.